{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b8e1d4f2-93a7-4c6e-a142-9f3b72c8d045",
    "name": "FinTrackPro API — Dev",
    "description": "Developer reference collection for FinTrackPro. Organized by resource — use for endpoint exploration, debugging, and manual testing during development.\n\n**NOT for CI.** Use `FinTrackPro.e2e.postman_collection.json` (via `bash scripts/api-e2e-local.sh`) for CI-gating tests.\n\nTest assertions are lightweight (status code + schema shape). `bearerToken` is minted automatically by the collection Pre-request Script — no manual token setup needed.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Import `FinTrackPro.postman_environment.json`\n2. Set `testUsername` / `testPassword` env vars if not using the default dev credentials\n3. Run any folder or individual request independently\n\n**Newman (ad hoc):**\n```bash\n# Full dev collection\nnewman run FinTrackPro.dev.postman_collection.json \\\n  -e FinTrackPro.postman_environment.json \\\n  --env-var \"baseUrl=http://localhost:5018\" \\\n  --env-var \"keycloakUrl=http://localhost:8080\" \\\n  --env-var \"testUsername=admin@fintrackpro.dev\" \\\n  --env-var \"testPassword=Admin1234!\" \\\n  -r cli\n\n# Single folder\nnewman run FinTrackPro.dev.postman_collection.json \\\n  -e FinTrackPro.postman_environment.json \\\n  --folder \"Trades\" \\\n  --env-var \"baseUrl=http://localhost:5018\" \\\n  --env-var \"keycloakUrl=http://localhost:8080\" \\\n  --env-var \"testUsername=admin@fintrackpro.dev\" \\\n  --env-var \"testPassword=Admin1234!\"\n```",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{bearerToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "exec": [
          "// Set testMonth once for the whole run (YYYY-MM of today).",
          "if (!pm.environment.get('testMonth')) {",
          "    const now = new Date();",
          "    const month = now.getFullYear() + '-' + String(now.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, '0');",
          "    pm.environment.set('testMonth', month);",
          "}",
          "",
          "// Refresh bearerToken if missing or expiring within 30 seconds.",
          "// Safe to do here (no 401 ordering requirement in the dev collection).",
          "const expiry = pm.environment.get('_tokenExpiry');",
          "if (!expiry || Date.now() > parseInt(expiry)) {",
          "    pm.sendRequest({",
          "        url: pm.environment.get('keycloakUrl')",
          "            + '/realms/fintrackpro/protocol/openid-connect/token',",
          "        method: 'POST',",
          "        header: { 'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' },",
          "        body: {",
          "            mode: 'urlencoded',",
          "            urlencoded: [",
          "                { key: 'grant_type', value: 'password' },",
          "                { key: 'client_id',  value: 'fintrackpro-e2e' },",
          "                { key: 'username',   value: pm.environment.get('testUsername') },",
          "                { key: 'password',   value: pm.environment.get('testPassword') }",
          "            ]",
          "        }",
          "    }, (err, res) => {",
          "        if (err) { throw new Error('Token mint failed: ' + err); }",
          "        const body = res.json();",
          "        if (!body.access_token) {",
          "            throw new Error('Token mint failed: ' + JSON.stringify(body));",
          "        }",
          "        pm.environment.set('bearerToken', body.access_token);",
          "        pm.environment.set('_tokenExpiry',",
          "            String(Date.now() + (body.expires_in - 30) * 1000));",
          "    });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Manual token mint example. The collection Pre-request Script handles token minting automatically — use this folder only to inspect or test the token endpoint directly.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Keycloak token (manual)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{keycloakUrl}}/realms/fintrackpro/protocol/openid-connect/token",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "password" },
                { "key": "client_id",  "value": "fintrackpro-e2e" },
                { "key": "username",   "value": "{{testUsername}}" },
                { "key": "password",   "value": "{{testPassword}}" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns access_token', () => {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('access_token');",
                  "  pm.expect(body).to.have.property('expires_in');",
                  "  // Optionally capture token for manual use:",
                  "  // pm.environment.set('bearerToken', body.access_token);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
